A '''shop foreman''' or '''plant foreman''' is a front-line [[supervisor]] in a [[tradesman|skilled trades]], [[manufacturing]] or [[production line|production]] operation: a person who plans, organizes and controls the operations of the shop or plant; supervises, trains and develops staff; provides advice to management and staff; and performs other duties. He will normally be experienced in the operations performed by the workers under supervision, and foremen are usually promoted from the [[wikt:rank and file|rank and file]] to perform this job; but the foreman is technically part of [[management]].

